# Node runtime (Cursor only)

Cursor agent shells often default to an old nvm Node (e.g. v18). That breaks Vitest, Biome, and `undici` here. Other harnesses usually already run Node 25 — they do not need extra nvm steps.

Before `npm run check`, `npm test`, or other Node commands in this repo:

```bash
nvm use    # reads .nvmrc (25); run `nvm install` once if missing
node -v    # should print v25.x
```

`npm run check` and `npm test` also run `check:node`, which fails fast on Node < 25.

## Cursor sandbox env

Agent shells inject `npm_config_devdir` and many `*CACHE*` paths under `cursor-sandbox-cache`. npm 11 warns on `devdir`, and offline installs inside macOS `sandbox-exec` can fail when those replace normal cache locations.

Repo scripts run child commands through `scripts/clean-npm-env.mjs`, which strips those variables. To avoid the one remaining npm warning, invoke checks directly:

```bash
nvm use
node scripts/clean-npm-env.mjs sh -c 'node scripts/check-node.mjs && vitest run'
```

Isolation/delegate tests use git worktrees and `sandbox-exec`; run them with full permissions, not the default sandbox.
